metadata.name: Swedish Forest #126
metadata.description:
If I had to choose a place where time was frozen and where I could contemplate the landscape for eternity this place would be a scandinavian forest.
I have been contemplating these kind of landscape for a very long time both in Sweden and in the Pyrenees where the ecosystem is very similar.
This project generates an illustration of a scandinavian forest in many different situations. At day and at night, in every season of the year, next to a lake or not, with steep hills or at the plains, snowing, with preponderance of some plant species over others, etc.
The artwork is also drawn in various paint modes and layouts.

The sun or the moon may be visible, the moon shows always the actual moon phase based on the current date.
The reflection on the lake is the fxhash morse endcoded.


Developed in vanilla js using svg and canvas
Rendering can be unresponsive on slow devices
Click or touch to switch to Parallax mode, just move the mouse or finger.


[S] Download in SVG format
[D] Download in PNG format

Features:

Layout: Landscape, Portrait, Square
PredominantSpecies: Blueberry, Lingonberry, Calluna, Rocks, None
Trees: Mixed, PinesAndFirs, Birches, None
Season: Spring, Summer, Fall, Winter
DayNight: Day, Night
PaintStyle: Normal, Stroke, Paint, WhiteOnBlack, BlackOnWhite
ColorStyle: Normal, Crazy
HasLake: True, False
HasTrees: None, Few, Many, Crowded

Created by Daniel Julià Lundgren, fxhash: danieljulia.tez, twitter: @daniel_julia. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: INTERFERENCES #191
metadata.description:
INTERFERENCES is an abstract representation of the incredible collaboration between artists, collectors and developers on fxhash.

Each edition is composed of a multitude of lines representing each individual on the platform. The color of each line defines the role of each individual in this universe. Through their interactions, and the interferences they produce, each line participates in the creation of a common work.

Happy birthday fxhash! And congratulations to all those who work for its success.

Primary sales are donated to the Processing Foundation

[TOUCHSCREEN]
* Double Tap to save the current image

[KEYBOARD]
* Press [S] to save the current image
* Press [1] to save a 1500x2000 pixels PNG
* Press [2] to save a 3000x4000 pixels PNG
* Press [3] to save a 6000x8000 pixels PNG
* Press [0] to save 3 individual SVG for each color set of lines + the background image PNG
* Press [9] to save a grouped SVG of all the lines + the background image PNG

Artist: Estienne
Nov. 2022
NFT License 2.0

Credits to Piter Pasma (@piterpasma) for the Reumann-Witkam line simplification algorithm used in this generator

metadata.name: Causality #68
metadata.description:
A response to the phenomenon of cause and effect. 

We think ourselves to be smart creatures for we have the ability to think, make decisions and communicate. And yet, we also often have to face the consequences of our past actions as we might have been short sighted in our purview in the past, maybe just as we might be even now. And we shall no not unless the future arrives. And to make matters a tiny bit more complex, my decisions might affect your reality and your decision may affect mine. 

We all understand causality, just like we understand Newton's third law of motion. The problem isn't in our understanding but in the limits we try to impose on it. For example, a person who doesn't wish to be short sighted will think of the future. But what does that mean? How exactly far out into the future should or even could a person think of? For you can always add another day to that same number hence making it quite the wicked problem. 

Causality ehh! A generative artwork made in cables.gl.

Press '1,2,3,4,5' to increase the resolution
Press 's' in LIVE mode to save a screenshot

Jaalibandar 2022

metadata.name: Choices & Tradeoffs #65
metadata.description:
Our entire life is a series of choices and tradeoffs.

Every day we make them - insignificant routine ones, or important life-changing ones. And every time we choose something - we automatically make a tradeoff, by definition. These concepts are heavily tied together. We reap the benefits of one decision, only to be throwing away all the others. But, which one are you supposed to pick? Well, that’s for each person to figure out by themselves.

There are no right or wrong choices. Just consequences.


Made with pure JS

metadata.name: Pare1d0scope #50
metadata.description:
Artwork.
Anchored in a not-so-binary world, the pare1d0scope generates unique patterns of 4-bit squares by applying a generative mix of color palettes, symmetry, ordering, subdividing, and diagonals adjustments.

Geometry.
The algorithm generates a sequence of the 2^4 possible 4-bits squares, adjusts inner diagonals, then draws them on a defined size canvas after applying specific color panels. Symmetry, ordering, and simpler black-and-white palets produce rarer iterations.

Shortcuts: [click] Adjust diagonals of selected 4-bit square iteration, [1-4] Adjust diagonals for all squares, [p] Print png.

Collaboration.
This project is a collaboration between sha22.art and Antonino.

metadata.name: Geometric Transcendence #47
metadata.description:
A series inspired by my time studying Orphism and the works of Robert Delaunay.

Geometric Transcendence experiments with carefully chosen palettes & structures in conjunction with a canvas-like texture that highlights the abstract characteristics of art during the Orphism movement.


In live mode, press 's' to save hi-res png (12000 x 16000px).


Great thanks to all collectors, supporters, and the fx(hash) community.


Made with p5js
Freeimp - October 2022

metadata.name: Separation in the Night #158
metadata.description:
For this project I was strongly inspired by the paintings of Mark Rothko, Jackson Pollock, Kazemir Malevich, but mostly token refers to the works of one of the largest figures of the European avant-garde, Paul Klee. I wanted to convey that complex color mood and atmosphere that artist achieved with oil paints. 
I have been working with color palettes and functions for a long time to make complex transitions and gradients. This code has really huge potential for a wide diversity of artworks and I would like to see as many interesting variations as possible. Enjoy<3

Project contains:

•three canvas types : horizontal, vertical, square
•rare features : vertical stripes, posterization
•press "p" to pause animation and play again
•open in tab and press "s" to save .png


Made in P5.js by @Georginerous

metadata.name: RushGushBlush #181
metadata.description:
Let's celebrate #fxhashturnsone with a cascade of colors!

This is just my second release on fxhash and I couldn't be happier to dedicate this project, however simple, to this amazing community.

I could go on describing the details of this piece but honestly I just wanted to create something very colorful for the party, without putting too many hidden meanings! :)
(Or maybe not...)

Happy birthday fxhash!

---

80% of primary sales will be donated to the Processing Foundation and Save Pakistan.

---

There are 17 different palettes and 3 formats, hope you'll find a combination that makes you happy!
The texture might look weird in thumbnails, so I recommend opening the piece in full screen and/or download the png by pressing "s".

---

By Todemashi 2022
NFT License 2.0

### NOTES
Made with p5js.
This project uses fx(stdio) by @alt_escapism - https://altesc.art/stdio
